# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NEPSE TRADING SYSTEM - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env to version control!
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════��═════════════════

# ── TELEGRAM CREDENTIALS ──────────────────────────────────────
# Get your BOT_TOKEN from @BotFather on Telegram
NEPSE_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here

# Get your CHAT_ID from @userinfobot on Telegram
NEPSE_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id_here

# ── API AUTHENTICATION ────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a secure API key (min 10 characters, recommended 32+)
# Use: openssl rand -hex 16
NEPSE_API_KEY=your_secure_api_key_minimum_10_chars

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL SETTINGS (Can be modified in config_final_optimized.py)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Trading mode: FINAL_OPTIMIZED | BALANCED | CONSERVATIVE | AGGRESSIVE
# TRADING_MODE=FINAL_OPTIMIZED

# Maximum daily loss in Rs. (negative number)
# MAX_DAILY_LOSS=-20000

# Circuit breaker max drawdown (as decimal, 0.10 = 10%)
# CIRCUIT_BREAKER_MAX_DD=0.10

# Position management
# MAX_POSITIONS=5
# MAX_PER_STOCK=1

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env with your credentials:
#    - Get BOT_TOKEN from @BotFather
#    - Get CHAT_ID from @userinfobot
#    - Generate API_KEY: openssl rand -hex 16
#
# 3. Set environment variables:
#    export $(cat .env | xargs)
#
# 4. Or source in your shell:
#    source .env
#
# 5. Start the system:
#    python main.py
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════